Comment: This is another game I had with the lovely MissLoly.
I played e5 in our previous game, so I do somethng different.
A good move, developing a piece to a good square and striking at f7.
So I blunt the power of that bishop.
Another good move, developing a piece.
So I "threaten" a queen side pawn expansion, but she can just ignore it, like she did.
She continues to develop.
So I attack.
Bishop drops back.
I hit the e pawn.
This protects the pawn, but d3 was a much better way of protecting it, as I can just drive the knight away.
So I attack the knight.
She moves it.
And i take, to go a clear pawn up.
This is another bad mistake, just giving up a knight.
So I just take.
She now attacks the bishop.
So I drop back.
And now she attacks the other bishop.
And that one drops back.
